          +o XmPACK_COLUMN. In PACK_COLUMN packing, children are      |
            placed in identically sized boxes so that the layout
            becomes a grid. The height of the boxes is the height
            of the highest child; similarly, the width of the boxes
            is the width of the widest child.

            The XXXXmmmmNNNNnnnnuuuummmmCCCCoooolllluuuummmmnnnnssss resource specifies how many columns    |
            (for XmVERTICAL orientation) or rows (for XmHORIZONTAL
            orientation) are built. There is no automatic wrapping
            when a column or row is too long to fit.                 |

